OL,3,CSculpture commemorates the Channel
OL,4,CIslands' witch trial victims
OL,6,FDr Adam Perchard said: "It's a hand
OL,7,Ffor every person that was there, so
OL,8,Fthat it works as an immediate visual
OL,9,Findication of how many people were
OL,10,Finvolved, people like us.
OL,12,F"It's a tree of human hands which in
OL,13,Fsome ways reminds one of the gallows
OL,14,Ftree, there's an element of the brutal
OL,15,Fto it but it's also very much an
OL,16,Femblem of healing."
OL,18,FDuring its creation, each volunteer
OL,19,Fwill be told the story of one of the
OL,20,Fvictims which their hand will
OL,21,Frepresent.
